When the news of the affair first appeared last year, Mr. Ensign apologized to his constituents and resigned as the fourth Republican leader in the Senate.
After months of stagnation, Mr. Ensign told reporters two weeks ago that he was planning to participate in a third term in the Senate.
In a report that Mr. Ensign is no longer the target of a criminal investigation, his spokeswoman Jennifer Cooper said the senator hopes the ethics committee will quickly follow the Justice Department and close the entire investigation.
"Senator Ensign is looking forward to continuing his hard work on behalf of the people of Nevada," she said.
